\fs30 \cf2 ##\cf4  Development
\fs24 \
\
To set up your environment to develop this theme, run \cf2 `\cf7 bundle install\cf2 `\cf4 .\
\
Your theme is setup just like a normal Jekyll site! To test your theme, run \cf2 `\cf7 bundle exec jekyll serve\cf2 `\cf4  and open your browser at \cf2 `\cf7 http://localhost:4000\cf2 `\cf4 . This starts a Jekyll server using your theme. Add pages, documents, data, etc. like normal to test your theme's contents. As you make modifications to your theme and to your content, your site will regenerate and you should see the changes in the browser after a refresh, just like normal.\
\
When your theme is released, only the files in \cf2 `\cf7 _layouts\cf2 `\cf4 , \cf2 `\cf7 _includes\cf2 `\cf4 , \cf2 `\cf7 _sass\cf2 `\cf4  and \cf2 `\cf7 assets\cf2 `\cf4  tracked with Git will be bundled.\
To add a custom directory to your theme-gem, please edit the regexp in \cf2 `\cf7 plainwhite.gemspec\cf2 `\cf4  accordingly.\
